\":\"rustling-beaming-porcupine\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"SessionStart\",\"hookName\":\"SessionStart:clear\",\"command\":\"bash ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/hooks/check-gopls.sh\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"734c4f9c-279e-494c-b222-3a8260aca4da\",\"toolUseID\":\"734c4f9c-279e-494c-b222-3a8260aca4da\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T03:31:28.279Z\",\"uuid\":\"a6399433-93c6-4443-b2e1-eaf75f3bac08\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"a6399433-93c6-4443-b2e1-eaf75f3bac08\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/gtrrz-victor/wks/cli/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"b8038f42-1ed7-418b-acc5-ef9a67f786ac\",\"version\":\"2.1.45\",\"gitBranch\":\"gtrrz-victor/github-copilot-support\",\"slug\":\"rustling-beaming-porcupine\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Plan: Add Copilot E2E Test Support\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe copilot agent is implemented and can be enabled via `entire enable --agent github-copilot`, but the e2e test suite (`cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/`) has no `CopilotRunner`. Running `E2E_AGENT=github-copilot` falls through to `unavailableRunner`. This plan adds copilot support so existing e2e scenarios work with `E2E_AGENT=github-copilot`.\\n\\nThe Copilot CLI (`copilot` v0.0.411) is installed locally and supports non-interactive mode via `-p \\\"prompt\\\"` with `--model` and `--allow-all-tools` flags — very similar to Claude Code.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. Add `CopilotRunner` to `e2e_test/agent_runner.go`\\n\\nAdd constant and runner:\\n\\n```go\\nconst AgentNameCopilot = \\\"github-copilot\\\"\\n```\\n\\n**`CopilotRunner` struct**: `Model string`, `Timeout time.Duration`\\n\\n**`NewCopilotRunner(config)`**:\\n- Model: `config.Model` || `E2E_COPILOT_MODEL` || `\\\"claude-haiku-4.5\\\"` (cheapest)\\n- Timeout: `config.Timeout` || `E2E_TIMEOUT` || `2m`\\n\\n**`IsAvailable()`**:\\n- `exec.LookPath(\\\"copilot\\\")`\\n- `copilot --version` with 10s timeout\\n\\n**`RunPromptWithTools(ctx, workDir, prompt, tools)`**:\\n- Command: `copilot --model <model> -p \\\"<prompt>\\\" --allow-all-tools`\\n- If `tools` provided: add `--available-tools <tools...>`\\n- Same stdout/stderr/exitcode capture pattern as `ClaudeCodeRunner`\\n\\n**`RunPrompt()`**: delegates to `RunPromptWithTools` with `nil` tools\\n\\n**Register in `NewAgentRunner` switch**:\\n```go\\ncase AgentNameCopilot:\\n    return NewCopilotRunner(config)\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Add copilot session dir env var to `e2e_test/testenv.go`\\n\\nThe copilot agent's `GetSessionDir()` checks `ENTIRE_TEST_COPILOT_SESSION_DIR`. Without it, hooks try to read `~/.copilot/session-state/` which won't have test session data.\\n\\nIn **3 methods** that set hook env vars — `GitCommitWithShadowHooks`, `GitCommitStagedWithShadowHooks`, `GitCommitWithTrailerRemoved` — add:\\n\\n```go\\n\\\"ENTIRE_TEST_COPILOT_SESSION_DIR=\\\" + filepath.Join(env.RepoDir, \\\".copilot-sessions\\\"),\\n```\\n\\nThis mirrors the existing `ENTIRE_TEST_CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR` and `ENTIRE_TEST_GEMINI_PROJECT_DIR` patterns.\\n\\n## Files\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|---|---|\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/agent_runner.go` | Add `AgentNameCopilot`, `CopilotRunner`, register in factory |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/testenv.go` | Add `ENTIRE_TEST_COPILOT_SESSION_DIR` to 3 hook env blocks |\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\n# Build and run a single e2e test with copilot\\nE2E_AGENT=github-copilot go test -tags=e2e -run TestE2E_BasicWorkflow ./cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/...\\n\\n# If copilot not authenticated, tests should skip gracefully (exit 0)\\n```\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/gtrrz-victor/.REDACTED.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"8f1311f1-a896-4cda-97de-91b7d024a2e5\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T03:31:27.554Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Plan: Add Copilot E2E Test Support\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe copilot agent is implemented and can be enabled via `entire enable --agent github-copilot`, but the e2e test suite (`cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/`) has no `CopilotRunner`. Running `E2E_AGENT=github-copilot` falls through to `unavailableRunner`. This plan adds copilot support so existing e2e scenarios work with `E2E_AGENT=github-copilot`.\\n\\nThe Copilot CLI (`copilot` v0.0.411) is installed locally and supports non-interactive mode via `-p \\\"prompt\\\"` with `--model` and `--allow-all-tools` flags — very similar to Claude Code.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. Add `CopilotRunner` to `e2e_test/agent_runner.go`\\n\\nAdd constant and runner:\\n\\n```go\\nconst AgentNameCopilot = \\\"github-copilot\\\"\\n```\\n\\n**`CopilotRunner` struct**: `Model string`, `Timeout time.Duration`\\n\\n**`NewCopilotRunner(config)`**:\\n- Model: `config.Model` || `E2E_COPILOT_MODEL` || `\\\"claude-haiku-4.5\\\"` (cheapest)\\n- Timeout: `config.Timeout` || `E2E_TIMEOUT` || `2m`\\n\\n**`IsAvailable()`**:\\n- `exec.LookPath(\\\"copilot\\\")`\\n- `copilot --version` with 10s timeout\\n\\n**`RunPromptWithTools(ctx, workDir, prompt, tools)`**:\\n- Command: `copilot --model <model> -p \\\"<prompt>\\\" --allow-all-tools`\\n- If `tools` provided: add `--available-tools <tools...>`\\n- Same stdout/stderr/exitcode capture pattern as `ClaudeCodeRunner`\\n\\n**`RunPrompt()`**: delegates to `RunPromptWithTools` with `nil` tools\\n\\n**Register in `NewAgentRunner` switch**:\\n```go\\ncase AgentNameCopilot:\\n    return NewCopilotRunner(config)\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Add copilot session dir env var to `e2e_test/testenv.go`\\n\\nThe copilot agent's `GetSessionDir()` checks `ENTIRE_TEST_COPILOT_SESSION_DIR`. Without it, hooks try to read `~/.copilot/session-state/` which won't have test session data.\\n\\nIn **3 methods** that set hook env vars — `GitCommitWithShadowHooks`, `GitCommitStagedWithShadowHooks`, `GitCommitWithTrailerRemoved` — add:\\n\\n```go\\n\\\"ENTIRE_TEST_COPILOT_SESSION_DIR=\\\" + filepath.Join(env.RepoDir, \\\".copilot-sessions\\\"),\\n```\\n\\nThis mirrors the existing `ENTIRE_TEST_CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR` and `ENTIRE_TEST_GEMINI_PROJECT_DIR` patterns.\\n\\n## Files\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|---|---|\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/agent_runner.go` | Add `AgentNameCopilot`, `CopilotRunner`, register in factory |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/testenv.go` | Add `ENTIRE_TEST_COPILOT_SESSION_DIR` to 3 hook env blocks |\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\n# Build and run a single e2e test with copilot\\nE2E_AGENT=github-copilot go test -tags=e2e -run TestE2E_BasicWorkflow ./cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/...\\n\\n# If copilot not authenticated, tests should skip gracefully (exit 0)\\n```\\n\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"8f1311f1-a896-4cda-97de-91b7d024a2e5\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/gtrrz-victor/wks/cli/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"b8038f42-1ed7-418b-acc5-ef9a67f786ac\",\"version\":\"2.1.45\",\"gitBranch\":\"gtrrz-victor/github-copilot-support\",\"slug\":\"rustling-beaming-porcupine\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01Uyt5JUjksm4kGTJgZkNJJq\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\n\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":12438,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":30583,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":12438},\"output_tokens\":9,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYGipPwrNLV4RA4iFwYkU\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"bbe2e9bb-a58c-439b-890c-4c67321394a6\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T03:31:31.108Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"bbe2e9bb-a58c-439b-890c-4c67321394a6\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/gtrrz-victor/wks/cli/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"b8038f42-1ed7-418b-acc5-ef9a67f786ac\",\"version\":\"2.1.45\",\"gitBranch\":\"gtrrz-victor/github-copilot-support\",\"slug\":\"rustling-beaming-porcupine\",\"message\":{\"mode