\":\"msg_01LcYVeYjq9XdFw1nncpBhg6\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The tests pass Claude Code tool names (`\\\"Write\\\"`, `\\\"Bash\\\"`) but Copilot uses different tool names. The solution is to have `CopilotRunner.RunPromptWithTools` translate Claude Code tool names to copilot equivalents, or just ignore the `tools` parameter since `--allow-all-tools` already grants everything.\\n\\nLet me check how Gemini handles this — it adds its own default tools and merges.\\n\\nLooking at the Gemini runner, it defines its own `defaultAllowedTools` and merges. For Copilot, we already pass `--allow-all-tools` which auto-approves everything, so `--available-tools` would actually *restrict* the available tools rather than allow them. The `--available-tools` flag in copilot means \\\"only these tools will be available\\\" — it's a restriction, not an allowlist.\\n\\nThe fix: `CopilotRunner` should ignore the `tools` parameter since `--allow-all-tools` already permits everything, and there's no meaningful way to map Claude's tool names to Copilot's.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1222,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":86153,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1222},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYGjzkZVEfqkMWA6fPdpF\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"4d81439b-bf1e-4b8c-bdf5-9880aca3228d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T03:47:04.352Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"4d81439b-bf1e-4b8c-bdf5-9880aca3228d\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/gtrrz-victor/wks/cli/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"b8038f42-1ed7-418b-acc5-ef9a67f786ac\",\"version\":\"2.1.45\",\"gitBranch\":\"gtrrz-victor/github-copilot-support\",\"slug\":\"rustling-beaming-porcupine\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01LcYVeYjq9XdFw1nncpBhg6\