ow branches store checkpoint data, carry-forward creates new shadow branches WITHOUT transcript metadata\\n   - The carry-forward second-commit condensation relies on reading transcript from `state.TranscriptPath` (live file on disk)\\n   - `handleLifecycleTurnStart` requires `event.SessionID` and returns error if empty — this fails silently for copilot's `userPromptSubmitted` hook\\n\\n3. Files and Code Sections:\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/agent_runner.go`** (MODIFIED)\\n     - Core file for agent test runners. Added CopilotRunner support.\\n     - Added constant: `const AgentNameCopilot = \\\"github-copilot\\\"`\\n     - Registered in factory switch: `case AgentNameCopilot: return NewCopilotRunner(config)`\\n     - Added full CopilotRunner implementation:\\n     ```go\\n     // CopilotRunner implements AgentRunner for GitHub Copilot CLI.\\n     type CopilotRunner struct {\\n         Model   string\\n         Timeout time.Duration\\n     }\\n\\n     func NewCopilotRunner(config AgentRunnerConfig) *CopilotRunner {\\n         model := config.Model\\n         if model == \\\"\\\" {\\n             model = os.Getenv(\\\"E2E_COPILOT_MODEL\\\")\\n             if model == \\\"\\\" {\\n                 model = \\\"claude-haiku-4.5\\\"\\n             }\\n         }\\n         // timeout logic same as other runners (E2E_TIMEOUT env or 2m default)\\n         // ...\\n         return &CopilotRunner{Model: model, Timeout: timeout}\\n     }\\n\\n     func (r *CopilotRunner) IsAvailable() (bool, error) {\\n         // exec.LookPath(\\\"copilot\\\") + copilot --version with 10s timeout\\n     }\\n\\n     func (r *CopilotRunner) RunPromptWithTools(ctx context.Context, workDir string, prompt string, _ []string) (*AgentResult, error) {\\n         // tools parameter ignored because Copilot tool names differ from Claude Code's\\n         // and --available-tools restricts rather than allows\\n         args := []string{\\\"--model\\\", r.Model, \\\"-p\\\", prompt, \\\"--allow-all-tools\\\"}\\n         // standard exec pattern with stdout/stderr capture\\n     }\\n     ```\\n   \\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/testenv.go`** (MODIFIED)\\n     - Added `ENTIRE_TEST_COPILOT_SESSION_DIR` to all 6 hook env blocks (prepare-commit-msg and post-commit in `GitCommitWithShadowHooks`, `GitCommitStagedWithShadowHooks`, `GitCommitWithTrailerRemoved`):\\n     ```go\\n     \\\"ENTIRE_TEST_COPILOT_SESSION_DIR=\\\"+filepath.Join(env.RepoDir, \\\".copilot-sessions\\\"),\\n     ```\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/copilot/types.go`** (READ)\\n     - Critical finding: `userPromptRaw` only has `hookBase` + `Prompt`. Only `agentStopRaw` has `SessionID` and `TranscriptPath`.\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/copilot/lifecycle.go`** (READ)\\n     - `parseTurnStart` returns Event with empty SessionID/SessionRef\\n     - `parseTurnEnd` returns Event with SessionID and SessionRef from agentStop stdin\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go`** (READ)\\n     - `handleLifecycleTurnStart` at line 120-123: requires `event.SessionID`, returns error if empty — this silently fails for copilot\\n     - `handleLifecycleTurnEnd` at line 162-165: falls back to `unknownSessionID` if empty\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`** (READ)\\n     - `CondenseSession` tries shadow branch first, falls back to live transcript\\n     - `extractSessionData` (line 370): tries `liveTranscriptPath` first, then shadow branch `metadataDir + \\\"/\\\" + paths.TranscriptFileName`\\n     - `carryForwardToNewShadowBranch` in hooks.go explicitly sets `MetadataDir: \\\"\\\"` — no transcript on carry-forward branch\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`** (READ)\\n     - `condenseAndUpdateState` resets StepCount, FilesTouched but preserves TranscriptPath\\n     - `carryForwardToNewShadowBranch` sets `StepCount=1`, `CheckpointTranscriptStart=0`, `LastCheckpointID=\\\"\\\"`\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/copilot/copilot.go`** (READ)\\n     - `GetSessionDir` checks `ENTIRE_TEST_COPILOT_SESSION_DIR` env override\\n     - `ResolveSessionFile` returns `filepath.Join(sessionDir, agentSessionID, \\\"events.jsonl\\\")`\\n\\n4. Errors and fixes:\\n   - **Edit tool non-unique string match**: When trying to append CopilotRunner after the GeminiCLIRunner, the string `result.ExitCode = 0\\\\n\\\\treturn result, nil\\\\n}` appeared twice (once for each runner). Fixed by using a larger, unique context string that included GeminiCLI-specific code.\\n   - **Copilot tool name mismatch (main fix)**: Tests passing Claude Code tool names (`\\\"Write\\\"`, `\\\"Bash\\\"`) to `RunPromptWithTools` caused copilot to report `Unknown tool name in the tool allowlist: \\\"Write\\\"` / `\\\"Bash\\\"`. Fixed by changing `tools []string` to `_ []string` in `RunPromptWithTools` and removing the `--available-tools` logic, since `--allow-all-tools` already grants all permissions.\\n   - **Second commit transcript missing (UNSOLVED)**: 6 remaining tests fail with \\\"Transcript not found at .../full.jsonl\\\" on the second commit in multi-commit scenarios. Root cause under investigation — appears related to copilot's lack of sessionId in userPromptSubmitted hook, which prevents proper session initialization via `InitializeSession`.\\n\\n5. Problem Solving:\\n   - **Solved**: Tool name mismatch — copilot uses different tool names and `--available-tools` restricts rather than allows. Fixed by ignoring tools parameter.\\n   - **Unsolved**: Second-commit transcript missing in 6 tests. Investigation traced through: condensation flow → carry-forward creates shadow branch without transcript → second commit must read from live transcript path → copilot's `userPromptSubmitted` has no sessionId so `InitializeSession` never runs → session state may be incomplete. The investigation was ongoing when the summary was requested.\\n   \\n   Passing tests (24): TestE2E_BasicWorkflow, TestE2E_MultipleChanges, TestE2E_CheckpointMetadata, TestE2E_CheckpointIDFormat